## Time Taken

~4 hours across 2 sessions (includes geometry debugging and component positioning)

---

## Why This Project

Built as the centrepiece CAD portfolio piece for SAE Thapar application (Aug 2026). The suspension corner was chosen specifically because it demonstrates multi-component assembly thinking, not just single-part modelling — and because double wishbone geometry is the foundation of every Formula Student car's chassis setup.
